Youtube link : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qxTdG44RgLE

in cmd prompt:
 1.npm install --global surge
 2.create a folder anywhere in local pc
 3.add that folder in visual code and create a new index.html file
 4.write your code in index.html file
 5.go to local PC. open that folder in cmd line(go inside the folder and replace that url with "cmd", press enter)
 6.it displays your project and path of folder
 7.check it and press type surge
 8.it displays domain name.. we can change if needed.(domain name syntax:name_of_domain.surge.sh)press enter
 9.success message will be displayed along with the url for created webpage.
 10.to make changes in created app,in cmd type
 surge --domain surgeBasicFolder.surge.sh press enter
  then do from step 6.
(if you are a new user, you should give mail ID and password to create account)


from visual studio code:

 to commit your code in surge:
 in visual studio code, open terminal
 type surge
 press enter
 it wil display the file path/location
 check it and press enter
 copy the url and open in chrome or else if needed we can rename the url by typing the command
   surge --domain surgeBasicFolder.surge.sh
 press enter
